<div class="text-wrap">
  <p>
    As for refining our value propositions: We interviewed a few members of the
    team to see how we talk about Segment internally. Turns out…  none of us really
    describe Segment in the same way :) It was clear that we’re not fully aligned
    on what the core value propositions of the product are. To fix that, we
    referred to the “Push” and “Pull” (or “Draw”) forces that came from the
    customer interviews we did a few weeks ago.
  </p>
</div>
<div class="work-image"><img src="/images/portfolio/segment-positioning/push-pull.png"></div>
<div class="text-wrap">
  <p>
    Those forces acted as a laundry list for the primary ways our customers are
    receiving value from Segment. We grouped those values by our customer cohorts
    (from customer jobs), common themes of the values, and made sure they lined
    up with our product vision.
  </p>
</div>
<div class="work-image"><img src="/images/portfolio/segment-positioning/approach.png"></div>
<div class="text-wrap">
  <p>
  We consolidated the larger list into a grouping of four value propositions
  that are core to the focus of our product.
  </p>

  <ul class="bulleted-list">
    <li>
    (You can) Use one API for tracking data
    </li>
    (We enable you to) Send your data to many tools and databases
    <li>
    (We also enable you to) Collect customer data from multiple sources
    </li>
    <li>
    (You can) Access and own your raw data
    </li>
  </ul>
</div>
<img src="/images/portfolio/segment-positioning/value-props.png">
<div class="text-wrap">
  <p>
    We found a parallel between the general order in which customers experience
    the values of our product and the order in which they experience pain points
    using data. As customers transition from the very beginning of getting their
    feet wet with analytics all the way to asking more complex questions of their
    data and need access to their raw data, we can see how the resulting timeline
    helps us know how to communicate the right information to our customers at
    the right time. It also helps us anticipate what their next steps might be
    and how we can help them be successful.
  </p>
</div>
<img src="/images/portfolio/segment-positioning/timeline.png">
