<div class="text-wrap">
  <p>
  For product, we have to think about how we we really nail the first value of
  using one API and sending data to multiple tools. If we don’t deliver on
  that, people won’t trust us to move up the chain. We also need to think of
  ways for people to discover the higher values and features as they “complete”
  or become experts in their current stage. 
  </p>
  <p>
  For sales, we can try to identify where a prospect is on the timeline, and
  sell them the value proposition that relates to the problem at hand. If they
  are low on the totem pole, we can hint at the values of Segment customers
  might run into down the line, but focus mostly on how we help them solve
  their current problem. Another thing we could do is try to pull in other
  members of the customer organization who might be able to better understand
  higher Stage values.
  </p>
  <p>
  For success, we can make sure our customers have an excellent experience
  solving their problems at each stage. We’ll be building help content that
  explains to them exactly how to do it, and where appropriate, we can offer
  advice in tickets to advance to the next level in.
  </p>
  <p>
  For marketing, we’ll be create content to speak to problems and offer
  solutions at each point of the timeline to attract new customers at different
  stages of their data maturity. Stay tuned for more on this with the new
  academy! We can also use this content in drip campaigns to help customers
  discover each new value and solve problems as they get deeper into using
  their data. We’ll be design the marketing site so it speaks to people both
  the in the early and late stages of knowledge, and using situations and
  problems to market pain points relevant features solve
  </p>
</div>
